Pharma Grade Sodium Lactate Solution Market Overview
The global sodium lactate market was valued at USD 259.5 million in 2021 and is projected to reach USD 536.3 million by 2030, growing at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 8.4% during the forecast period. This growth is driven by the increasing demand for sodium lactate in various industries, including pharmaceuticals, food and beverages, and cosmetics. The pharmaceutical sector, in particular, utilizes sodium lactate in intravenous solutions and dialysis treatments, contributing significantly to market expansion. Additionally, the rising consumer preference for natural and clean-label ingredients in personal care products further boosts the demand for sodium lactate.

